help with depression general social anxiety anger i have been suffering with depression ever since i had an abortion and it eventually lead to me closing myself in from the world and i've gotten a lot of social anxiety lately i cant even walk into a store or a room full of people without walking awkwardly freezing between steps and looking at the floor i can't help it i just can't feel normal anymore also i'm starting to get really emotional even when little things go wrong does anyone know what i can do does seeing a psychiatrist or getting counseling really help do the medications really help thanks seeing a counselor really does help some people i can't say it will help you but it is worth a try my daughter suffers from the same disorders she sees a counselor and is taking zoloft her life became so much better and happier she can deal with problems and challenges easily now she hates that she has to take these meds to feel more normal but i explained to her that it was like she just had a missing piece to a puzzle and now it is complete she may not always need the meds but for now it works i wish you so much luck and i hope you find the help you need Anxiety Clinical depression Psychotherapy Chronic fatigue syndrome Borderline personality disorder Psychoanalysis Asperger syndrome Bipolar disorder Charles Darwin's illness Sigmund Freud Panic attack Eating disorder Anorexia nervosa Obsessive-compulsive disorder Antidepressant Transsexuality Traumatic brain injury Alcoholism Controversies in autism Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Mental illness Autism Multiple sclerosis Transactional analysis Insomnia Psychiatry Drug addiction The Curse of Fenric Stuttering Reparative therapy Pitaten Oh My Goddess! Phobia Abortion Social anxiety Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Baldness Rational Emotive Behavior Therapy Sertraline Philosophical counseling Nicomachean Ethics Premature ejaculation Gender identity disorder EastEnders Boston Public Social rule Antisocial p